    <etym xml:lang="ru">Сопоставляется с <mentioned xml:lang="goh"
                    ><lang/><w>felawa</w><gloss><q>ива</q></gloss></mentioned>. Идеосемантика ведет
        либо к „влаге“, „болоту“ и т. п. („влаголюбивое дерево“), ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>palvala-</w><gloss><q>пруд</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>лужа</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><lang/><w>palūs</w><gloss><q>болото</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>E.
                Liden</author><ref target="#ref_IF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">18, стр.
                486</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">18, p. 486</biblScope></bibl>), либо к
        понятию „серого“ (по цвету коры, листвы): <mentioned xml:lang="de"
            ><lang/><w>fahl</w></mentioned> и пр. (<bibl><author>F. Holthausen</author><ref
                target="#ref_IF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">25, стр. 150</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">25, p. 150</biblScope></bibl>); сюда же в этом случае %i*fæl-%i в <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_fælūrs"/> ‘бледный’.%n<bibl><author>Kretschmer</author><ref
                target="#ref_KZ"/><biblScope>XXXI 427</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 86</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Walde"/><biblScope>557</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>32</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It is compared with <mentioned xml:lang="goh"
                    ><lang/><w>felawa</w><gloss><q>willow</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ideosemantics
        leads either to ‘moisture’, ‘swamp’, etc. (‘moisture-loving tree’), cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>palvala-</w><gloss><q>pond</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>puddle</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><lang/><w>palūs</w><gloss><q>swamp</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>E.
                Liden</author><ref target="#ref_IF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">18, стр.
                486</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">18, p. 486</biblScope></bibl>), or to the
        concept of ‘gray’ (according to the color of the bark and foliage): <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                ><lang/><w>fahl</w></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><author>F. Holthausen</author><ref
                target="#ref_IF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">25, стр. 150</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">25, p. 150</biblScope></bibl>); in this case see also %i*fæl-%i in
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fælūrs"/> ‘pale’.%n<bibl><author>Kretschmer</author><ref
                target="#ref_KZ"/><biblScope>XXXI 427</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 86</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Walde"/><biblScope>557</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>32</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
